# Git Checkout All - Target Branches Configuration
# 
# This file defines which branches should be updated when using the --pull flag
# with git-fetch-all or git-fetch-one commands.
#
# Configuration Methods (in priority order):
# 1. Environment Variable:
#    export GIT_CHECKOUT_ALL_TARGET_BRANCHES="develop,staging,main"
#
# 2. Config File (this file):
#    Copy this file to: ~/.git-checkout-all.conf
#
# 3. Default (if no configuration found):
#    develop-pjp, develop, staging, master
#
# Format:
# - One branch per line, OR
# - Comma-separated list on one or multiple lines
# - Lines starting with # are comments
# - Empty lines are ignored
#
# Examples:

# Method 1: One branch per line (recommended)
develop-pjp
develop
staging
master

# Method 2: Comma-separated (alternative)
# develop-pjp,develop,staging,master

# Method 3: Mixed format
# develop-pjp, develop
# staging, master

# Add your custom branches:
# main
# production
# release
